<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832596>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. Parkermavella columnaris sp. nov., holotype (NIWA 97418), Recent, inferred greater Cook Strait, New Zealand. A. Group of ovicellate zooids. B. Tilted close-up of an autozooid showing the broadly cleithridiate (keyhole shaped) orifice, four distal oral spines, two of which coalescent, and the suboral avicularium with complete cross-bar. C. Lateral view of the columnar peristome bearing the suboral avicularium. D. Inner view of the frontal shield showing the umbonuloid area and ring scar. Scale bars: A = 250 µm; B = 100 µm; C–D = 50 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3832596/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832598>
    dc:description "Fig. 3. Parkermavella columnaris sp. nov. A–C. Paratype (NHMUK PI BZ 7832), Castlecliffian, Pleistocene, Upper Kai-Iwi Shellbed, New Zealand. A. View of a small colony. B. Group of autozooids. C. Two ovicellate zooids. D. Paratype (NHMUK PI BZ 7833), same provenance as preceding, inner view of the frontal shield showing part of the ring scar bordering the umbonuloid area. Scale bars: A = 500 µm; B–C = 100 µm; D = 50 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3832598/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

